page.title: 09LAND IN MYDDLE
page.content: {WOODS} We have got one big wood in{MYDDLE},it runs all the way down {LOWER ROAD},a lane which runs along the side of{ {MYDDLE . { } {LANDSCAPE The{LANDSCAPE}in{MYDDLE}is mostly {FARM LAND}though there is some land with houses on. Most of the FARM LAND is being grazed and not being cut for silage but the land is being cut for silage further out of the village where the small farmers farm.Only a few people are using land for hay as it is not very popular.They vary in size from about 10 acres to 20 acres.You can not see any{OIL SEED RAPE}and there are very few corn fields.There are two fields that are newly seeded but there may be more.
